-- MOVES-EY hires former Booz & Co exec to lead public sector practice
-- 
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 08:55AM EDT
-- None



Aug 11 (Reuters) - Audit firm EY, formerly known as Ernst & Young, named George Atalla to the role of global sector leader to its government and public sector practice.

Atalla was a partner and vice president at consultancy firm Booz & Co where he led its government public sector practice across the Middle East and Africa. Atalla succeeds Uschi Schreiber and will be based in EY's McLean, Virginia office.